The Limpopo government has halted another multi-million-rand shack project in Burgersfort. eNCA reporter Manqoba Mchunu is following that story for us and joins us now. Courtesy #DStv403 POLOKWANE - The multi-million rand Limpopo shoddy housing scandal has taken a new turn. The Limpopo government has halted a multi-million rand shack project in Burgersfort. READ: SIU to probe Limpopo shack project The 50 structures, similar to the ones handed over to Talana residents in Tzaneen last month, is believed to have cost the Limpopo government at least R17-million. Residents in the area are allegedly refusing to occupy the units.